    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Does it mean that as long as the public address of an unlocked account has been acquired once, the exposure is permanent even without the need of obtaining the private key?  Subsequently, this attack is possible whenever the port 8545 is opened in the earlier provided geth command and at the same time the account is unlocked?  Lastly, is there a way to obtain and/or cancel the many pre-signed transactions by the identified attacker?  Thanks.   ",
