    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "If at _any time_ an attacker is able to sign transactions for an account (e.g. through an unlocked account on an Ethereum node), that account is vulnerable forever and must be abandoned.  Once the attacker has the signed transactions in-hand, they don't need any access to your node in order to drain the funds.  There is no way to cancel presigned transactions.",
